I think I've found a better solution that aligns more closely with the behavior of rendering: https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/32282/commits/052a6d51d82ec7fa730ea401648f4cb522f67e56

By setting `finder.formats`, we avoid the need to find with a `:formats` option. And when it's set to `[:js]`, we automatically get an `:html` fallback:
https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/d9736e50d8d6fc9fad32e16ebdc8dcd0a0a3ec61/actionview/lib/action_view/lookup_context.rb#L245-L255

Rendering a request works similarly: https://github.com/rails/rails/blob/d9736e50d8d6fc9fad32e16ebdc8dcd0a0a3ec61/actionview/lib/action_view/rendering.rb#L106-L111

