@brianknight10 I wonder if we're going about this the wrong way - the S3 client will do all of this credential resolution for us if we don't supply the access_key_id, secret_access_key and region options. What if we just change the `initialize` method to this:

``` ruby
def initialize(bucket:, upload: {}, **options)
  @client = Aws::S3::Resource.new(**options)
  @bucket = @client.bucket(bucket)

  @upload_options = upload
end
```

This allows you to specify a profile in your storage.yml file then, e.g:

``` yaml
s3:
 service: S3
 bucket: "activestorage"
 profile: "rails"
```

Also the all the environment vars will work too without us having to think about it. If you still want to explicitly add the access details to the YAML file then that still works too.

